Bankia in Talks to Sell 20% of Grupo Genesa to EDP, Expansion Reports

-- B y   S h a r o n   S m y t h
-- 
2011-03-21T06:41:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-21/bankia-in-talks-to-sell-20-of-grupo-genesa-to-edp-expansion-reports.html
Bankia, the bank formed from a
merger of seven savings banks led by  Caja Madrid , is in advanced
talks to sell its 20 percent stake in Grupo Genesa to  EDP
Renovaveis SA (EDPR) ,  Expansion  reported, without citing anyone.  The stake in the renewable energy company is valued at
around 300 million euros ($425 million), the newspaper said.  Link to Company News:  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Smyth in Madrid at 
 ssmyth2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Blackman at   ablackman@bloomberg.net . 